# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../titles.rst:167
msgid "Custom Title Templates"
msgstr "Egendefinerte tittelskabeloner"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../titles.rst:168
msgid ""
"OpenShot can use any vector SVG image file as a custom title template in "
"the :guilabel:`Title Editor` dialog. Just add an SVG image file to your ``~/."
"openshot_qt/title_templates/`` folder, and it will appear the next time you "
"launch the :guilabel:`Title Editor` dialog. You can also right click on any "
"SVG files in your **Project Files** panel, and choose **Edit Title** or "
"**Duplicate Title**."
msgstr ""
"OpenShot kan bruke hvilken som helst vektor-SVG-bildefil som en egendefinert "
"tittelskabelon i :guilabel:`Tittelredigerings`-dialogen. Bare legg til en "
"SVG-bildefil i mappen ``~/.openshot_qt/title_templates/``, så vil den vises "
"neste gang du åpner :guilabel:`Tittelredigerings`-dialogen. Du kan også "
"høyreklikke på SVG-filer i **Prosjektfiler**-panelet og velge **Rediger "
"tittel** eller **Dupliser tittel**."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../titles.rst:172
msgid ""
"Note: These SVG templates are only used by the :guilabel:`Title Editor` "
"dialog, and not :guilabel:`Animated Title` dialog."
msgstr ""
"Merk: Disse SVG-malene brukes kun av :guilabel:`Tittelredigerings`-dialogen, "
"og ikke :guilabel:`Animerte tittel`-dialogen."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../titles.rst:177
msgid "3D Animated Titles"
msgstr "3D-animerte titler"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../titles.rst:178
msgid ""
"Adding a 3D animated title is just as easy, using our **Animated Title** "
"dialog. Use the Title menu (located in the main menu of OpenShot) to launch "
"the Animated Title editor. You can also use the keyboard shortcut "
"**Ctrl+B**. Note: Blender must be installed and configured before this "
"feature will work in OpenShot. See :ref:`blender_install_ref`."
msgstr ""
"Å legge til en 3D-animasjonstittel er like enkelt ved å bruke vår **Animerte "
"tittel**-dialog. Bruk Tittel-menyen (i hovedmenyen i OpenShot) for å åpne "
